                        div#about-me-text
                            p.content-text.intro-text Hi! I’m Charlie Yin, a software developer currently based in Vancouver, British Columbia.
                            p.content-text.detail-text I graduated from the University of British Columbia, receiving a Bachelor of Electrical Engineering in 2017. Even though I studied as an electrical engineer, I actually became more and more interested in the software side of things. I’ve worked on different projects throughout the years, some of which include developing firmware for robots, implementing distributed real-time networks, and even making an AI for learning text patterns. I'm most proficient in C/C++, though I do have a good working knowledge of JavaScript, Python, and many more. My current interest lies in firmware development and machine learning/artificial intelligence.
                            p.content-text.detail-text Aside from software, I also have a big interest in music. I listen to a ton of jazz, with recordings dating back all the way to the 40's, and I'll frequently practice jazz piano as a side hobby.

