                                    div.project-description
                                        a(href="https://ubcsailbot.org/")
                                            div.project-title UBC Sailbot
                                            p UBC’s autonomous sailboat. I worked with a team to implement a distributed real-time network in C/C++ for sensor data transfer over the CAN bus using the CANopen protocol. The result is a reliable network which can support up to 127 separate nodes.
                                li.project-item
                                    div.project-image
                                        video(loop muted preload data-url="./videos/gyro.mp4").project-video
                                        img(src="./images/index/gyro.jpg" alt="Gyro Stabilized Platform").pixelated
                                        div.load-circle-container.circle-load
                                            div.load-circle
                                        div.load-circle-container.stroke-load
                                            svg
                                                circle(cx="50%" cy="50%" r="45%").load-stroke
                                    div.project-description
                                        a(href="https://github.com/CharlieYJH/self-balance-platform")
                                            div.project-title Gyro Stabilized Platform
                                            p A self-stabilizing platform. I implemented the software in C++ which allowed the platform to self-stabilize within +/-1° of the horizontal in less than 2s with an overshoot or undershoot of no more than +/-4°, all while supporting a weight of up to 200g.
                                li.project-item
                                    div.project-image
                                        video(loop muted preload data-url="./videos/helicopter.mp4").project-video
                                        img(src="./images/index/helicopter.jpg" "Self-Correcting Helicopter").pixelated
                                        div.load-circle-container.circle-load
                                            div.load-circle
                                        div.load-circle-container.stroke-load
                                            svg
                                                circle(cx="50%" cy="50%" r="45%").load-stroke
                                    div.project-description
                                        a(href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hKBk48Tjly0")
                                            div.project-title Self-Correcting Helicopter
                                            p A self-correcting helicopter model. I worked with a partner to implement the PID control in C++ necessary for the 2-DOF helicopter to recover from external disturbances in both the pitch and yaw directions. The final product recovers from any external disturbance quickly and with minimal oscillations.
                                li.project-item
                                    div.project-image
                                        video(loop muted preload data-url="./videos/homepage.mp4").project-video
                                        img(src="./images/index/homepage.png" alt="Personal Homepage").pixelated
                                        div.load-circle-container.circle-load
                                            div.load-circle
                                        div.load-circle-container.stroke-load
                                            svg
                                                circle(cx="50%" cy="50%" r="45%").load-stroke
                                    div.project-description
